# TTF Scaffolding Co. Ltd.  
**Level 1 East Suspended Slab Shoring Plan, Section & Details**  
**Job Location:** Terra Garden, 15258 102A Avenue, Surrey, B.C.  
**Contractor:** Leading Edge Concrete Ltd.  
**Date:** September 21, 2024  
**Drawn by:** F.T.  
**Contact:** 10979 Olsen Road, Surrey, BC, V3V 3S9  
**Phone:** 778-898-5301  
**Email:** info@ttfscaffolding.com  
**Website:** www.ttfscaffolding.com  

---

## 1. General Information

This document outlines the specifications and requirements for the shoring plan associated with the Level 1 East Suspended Slab. All dimensions and elevations must be verified by the contractor prior to the shipment of equipment.

## 2. Concrete Specifications

- **Concrete Type:** 50 MPa C-XL
- **Slab Thickness:** 14 inches (typical)
- **Load Capacity:** 
  - Flat Slab: 225 psf (pounds per square foot)
  - Drop Panels: 350 psf

## 3. Shoring and Framing Details

### 3.1 Shoring System

- **Wood Joists:** 4x6 lumber, spaced at 16 inches on center (O/C)
- **Bracing:** All frames shall be 6 feet high and 4 feet wide, heavy-duty (10K/leg) with 7-foot bracing.
- **Post Shores:** #4 post shore, maximum spacing of 4 feet O/C.

### 3.2 Slab Band

- **Dimensions:** 8 feet by 24 inches
- **Location:** As indicated on the drawings.

### 3.3 Wood Wedge

- **Type:** Standard wood wedge, typical use throughout the shoring system.

### 3.4 Inspection Requirements

- **Pre-Pour Inspection:** Required by the undersigned Professional Engineer prior to pouring concrete.

## 4. Notes

- **No Shore Requirement:** No shoring is required under the slab or slab band unless marked as "X" for #2 or "[X]" for #4 post shore on the plan.
- **Plywood Specifications:** Minimum thickness of 3/4 inch Douglas Fir #1 or better.
- **Joist Usage:** 4x6 wood joists supplied by TTF Scaffolding shall not be used for packing or cut short for other purposes.
- **Reshoring:** All reshoring must align with the step line up with the wall above.

## 5. Additional Information

- **Related Drawings:** Refer to structural drawing (by supplier) for hollow core panels over the detention tank.
- **Revision History:** For any revisions, please refer to the accompanying documentation.

## 6. Scale

- **Drawing Scale:** 3/16 inch = 1 foot

---

**Disclaimer:** This drawing must be read in conjunction with architectural and structural drawings. The contractor is responsible for confirming all dimensions and elevations prior to equipment shipment.
